## Cole Sebeol Specification

Hisle's Cole Sebeol key map is an independent transcription of the Gong
Byung-woo Sebeolsik Final layout into Hisle's own specification format.

The Gong Byung-woo Sebeolsik Final layout is a functional keyboard layout. Hisle
uses it as the basis for Hangul jamo key assignments and documents project
specific behavior in `hisle-core/Sources/HisleCore/Resources/cole-sebeol-spec.txt`.

The libhangul project (LGPL 2.1) was consulted for Unicode Hangul values,
Sebeolsik layout data, and behavior comparison. Hisle does not vendor libhangul
code or XML data, and it does not link to libhangul.

Hisle's Unicode Hangul syllable composition code follows the algorithmic Hangul
composition model specified by the Unicode Standard.

## Development References

The Gureum input method project (BSD/LGPL) was used as a reference for macOS
Korean input-method implementation patterns, including InputMethodKit behavior.
Hisle does not vendor Gureum code or assets.
